Question	Answer
What is the name of the college?	Vishwakarma University Pune.
Where is the college located?	The college is located in Kondhwa, Pune, Maharashtra.
When was the college established?	It was established in the year 2017.
What courses are offered?	The university offers courses in Engineering, Management, Law, Design, Commerce, Arts, and Science.
What is the admission process?	You can apply online through the official admission portal or visit the campus admission office.
What is the contact number?	You can contact the college at +91-20-26950502.
What facilities are available?	Facilities include library, laboratories, hostel, sports complex, cafeteria, Wi-Fi campus, and innovation labs.
Who is the principal?	Dr. Ashwin Deshpande is the principal of the university.
What is the college website?	The official website is https://www.vupune.ac.in
What is the email address?	You can email the college at info@vupune.ac.in
What are the hostel facilities?	The hostel provides clean rooms, Wi-Fi, canteen, security, and recreational areas.
Does the college provide placement assistance?	Yes, the college has a dedicated placement cell that helps students get placed in reputed companies.
What is the average placement package?	The average package ranges from 4 LPA to 8 LPA depending on the program.
What companies visit for placement?	Top companies like Infosys, TCS, Tech Mahindra, Wipro, and Accenture visit the campus.
What are the college timings?	College timings are from 9:00 AM to 4:30 PM.
Does the college have a canteen?	Yes, there is a hygienic canteen providing vegetarian and non-vegetarian food.
Is there a library?	Yes, the university has a digital and physical library with thousands of books and research papers.
Does the college have Wi-Fi?	Yes, the entire campus is Wi-Fi enabled.
Are there sports facilities?	Yes, the college has indoor and outdoor sports facilities including cricket, football, basketball, and gym.
What is the dress code?	Formal or semi-formal attire is recommended. Some departments have specific uniforms.
What are the eligibility criteria for engineering?	Students must have completed 12th with Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics with minimum 50% marks.
What scholarships are available?	Scholarships are available based on merit, sports, and category (SC/ST/OBC/EWS).
Who is the founder of the university?	The founder is Shri Vishwakarma Group of Institutions.
Is there a transportation facility?	Yes, buses are available for students from different parts of the city.
What extracurricular activities are conducted?	The college conducts cultural fests, hackathons, technical events, and seminars.
When does the new academic year start?	The new academic session usually starts in July every year.
